<node id="Trigger">
  <data key="d0">Trigger</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Trigger refers to the underlying cause of feeling paralyzed or anxious about creative tasks, typically relating to fears or uncertainties.&lt;SEP&gt;Trigger is a concept referring to specific circumstances or cues that prompt the use of different creative methods.&lt;SEP&gt;Trigger refers to the specific conditions or feelings that prompt the use of various creative methods in The Creative Habit.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d7fecbb0e15b0c2fecb3e2017d03f5ce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f5bfa64481a8d63180f365f8cb3d39ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-324826e69646e9a60494746cffe0957b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774652538</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Timer">
  <data key="d0">Timer</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Timer represents a concept related to creating structure in the creative process, indicating a specific duration for tasks.&lt;SEP&gt;Timer denotes the time duration set for each creative method or exercise to maintain focus and structure.&lt;SEP&gt;Timer is a concept used in the exercises to define the time limits for completing tasks and fostering rapid idea generation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d7fecbb0e15b0c2fecb3e2017d03f5ce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f5bfa64481a8d63180f365f8cb3d39ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-324826e69646e9a60494746cffe0957b</data>
